body:
Hi Support Team,

Thanks for the quick response. You can find the code snippet below:

```mercury
async function myFunc() {
console.log('Starting...');
await sleep(1000); // Wait for 1 second
console.log('Finished!');
}

myFunc();
console.log('This should appear before 'Finished!');
```

I'm currently using Mercury version 2.3.1.

Thanks,
John

